        frq: { type: "Chi-Square Test for Association FRQ", prompt: "A two-way table shows smoking habits and exercise frequency for 200 adults. Test whether smoking and exercise are independent at α = 0.05. Complete the full 4-step procedure: hypotheses, conditions (with expected counts), χ² calculation, and conclusion.", rubricTip: "Computing expected counts and verifying they are all ≥ 5 earns a separate rubric point. Show at least one expected count calculation: Expected = (row total)(column total)/grand total." },
        tip: "On the AP exam, chi-square tests and two-sample inference are often paired with an interpretive question: 'What would it mean if you committed a Type I error in this context?' or 'Describe a Type II error and explain its consequences.' Practice answering these in plain language.",
